{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771421302,"nonce":"AS9YP+bhOv5qmhUqpFu/EGhFDkQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87r6F4d","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/225","origin":"github"},"title":"detect_cli_env.sh false-positives: regular terminals detected as Claude Code agent","message":"## Problem\n\nWhen a regular user sources `.agent/scripts/env.sh` from a normal terminal, it incorrectly detects them as a Claude Code agent and overrides their git identity with the agent identity (`Claude Code Agent \u003croland+claude-code@ccom.unh.edu\u003e`).\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`detect_cli_env.sh` uses overly broad heuristics for Claude Code detection:\n\n1. **Line 72**: Checks `$ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` and `$CLAUDE_API_KEY` — these are API credentials that users commonly have in their shell profile, not indicators that we're running inside Claude Code.\n2. **Lines 85-97**: Falls back to checking if the `claude` CLI is installed and `claude --version` works — having the tool installed doesn't mean we're running inside it.\n\nEither condition causes `env.sh` (line 136-138) to call `set_git_identity_env.sh --detect`, which overrides the user's git identity for the session.\n\n## Proposed Fix\n\nIn `detect_cli_env.sh`:\n\n- **Remove** `$ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` and `$CLAUDE_API_KEY` from the Claude Code detection check on line 72. Only `$CLAUDE_CODE` is a reliable signal (Claude Code sets this when it spawns subshells).\n- **Remove or gate** the fallback `claude` command check (lines 85-97). Having the CLI installed is not evidence of running inside it.\n\nAfter the fix, line 72 should be:\n```bash\nif [ -n \"$CLAUDE_CODE\" ]; then\n```\n\nAnd the fallback block (lines 85-97) should be removed or guarded by additional evidence.\n\n## Impact\n\nAny user who has `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` set or `claude` CLI installed gets their git identity silently overridden every time they source `env.sh`.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}